==========================================================
STEP 1: ONNX EXPORT (SPEED)
==========================================================

Deep Learning models are trained using PyTorch (Python). 
Python is slow. 

To deploy AegisNet to the frontline firewall, we run our 
`onnx_exporter.py` script. This translates the complex 
neural network into an Open Neural Network Exchange (ONNX) 
computational graph.

Benefits:
  - Language Agnostic (can run in C++, Rust, Go)
  - Hardware Accelerated (direct GPU/Tensor Core access)
  - Latency drops to < 15 milliseconds.


==========================================================
STEP 2: DATA DRIFT DETECTION (ACCURACY)
==========================================================

"Data Drift" happens when the real world changes, making 
your old AI obsolete.

Our `drift_monitor.py` script calculates the "Wasserstein 
Distance" between two datasets:
  1. The baseline Kaggle dataset we trained on last month.
  2. The actual live traffic hitting the company today.

If the mathematical distance between these two datasets 
exceeds a certain threshold, it means attackers are using 
new techniques. The system flags the SOC to collect new 
malware samples and retrain the models.


